last_episode_to_air.name: End of the World
last_episode_to_air.overview: The fate of the world is decided as the long journey of a preacher and his friends comes to an end.

name: Preacher
overview: A preacher sets out on a mission to make the almighty himself confess his sin of abandoning the world. With his best friend Cassidy, an alcoholic Irish vampire, his love Tulip, a red blooded gun towing Texan, and the power of genesis, an unholy child born from an angel and a devil, Jesse gives up everything to set the world straight with its creator.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Jesse Custer, a conflicted Preacher in a small Texas town who is inhabited by a mysterious entity that allows him to develop a highly unconventional power. Jesse, his ex-girlfriend, Tulip, and an Irish vampire named Cassidy embark on a journey to, literally, find God.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In Season 2, after Jesse accidentally discovered that God is absent from Heaven, the three of them set out on a road trip to find Him, all while being hunted by the Saint of Killers, an unstoppable, mythical killer from Hell. The trio’s pursuit led them to New Orleans, where they dodged local gangsters, dangerous agents, and other unimaginable mayhem on their way to uncovering an even bigger secret. Now, with Tulip’s life and Cassidy’s friendship in the balance, Jesse must rely on a mysterious figure from his past in order to save his friends and continue on with his mission.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: In Season 3, Jesse Custer’s quest for God takes him back to the place he’s been avoiding his whole life: home. Jesse, Tulip, and Cassidy return to Angelville, the Louisiana Plantation where Jesse was raised, and find old grudges and deadly obligations await them. With the help of his friends — and a few enemies — Jesse will need to escape his past… because the future of the world depends on it.

tagline: IT all goes to hell in the end.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: A preacher heads out on a journey to combat the supernatural evil that just decimated his Texas hometown.

episodes.name: See
episodes.overview: Jesse tries to be a "good preacher," unaware that a mysterious duo is after him. Meanwhile, the enigmatic Cowboy is introduced.

episodes.name: The Possibilities
episodes.overview: Jesse explores his newfound power with Cassidy's help. Meanwhile, armed with new information, Tulip tries to convince Jesse to set out for revenge.

episodes.name: Monster Swamp
episodes.overview: Jesse makes Quincannon a bet he can't refuse; and Cassidy works to fend off the angels. Meanwhile, Tulip tries to bring justice to Annville.

episodes.name: South Will Rise Again
episodes.overview: After his stunt with Quincannon, Jesse is Annville's newest rock star; and Tulip and Cassidy connect. Meanwhile, the Cowboy makes a tragic decision.

episodes.name: Sundowner
episodes.overview: Jesse finally comes face to face with Deblanc and Fiore and learns about the mysterious entity that has taken over his body.

episodes.name: He Gone
episodes.overview: Jesse's actions alienate and endanger those closest to him as we glimpse into his past and finally learn the root of all of his guilt.

episodes.name: El Valero
episodes.overview: Jesse protects his church in a vicious gun battle against Quincannon and the Meat Men; Tulip hopes to save a friend.

episodes.name: Finish the Song
episodes.overview: Jesse's in the wind while those close to him face life-changing decisions; the Cowboy comes back to Ratwater seeking his revenge.

episodes.name: Call and Response
episodes.overview: Jesse hopes to follow through on his promise to obtain answers from heaven; the entire town waits with bated breath.

episodes.name: On the Road
episodes.overview: Jesse, Tulip, and Cassidy begin the search to find God. The trio realize they are being followed by a killer cowboy from Hell.

episodes.name: Mumbai Sky Tower
episodes.overview: Jesse, Tulip, and Cassidy track a lead from Heaven. The trio tries to find out who the Cowboy is and why he's attempting to kill them.

episodes.name: Damsels
episodes.overview: Jesse, Tulip, and Cassidy get a tip that God may be in New Orleans. Tulip is hiding a secret and their stop in New Orleans risks exposing her.

episodes.name: Viktor
episodes.overview: Jesse pursues a lead and dives deeper into his search for God with Cassidy and we discover more about Tulip's secret past.

episodes.name: Dallas
episodes.overview: After learning about Tulip's secret relationship, we revisit Jesse and Tulip's rocky past and see a darker side of Jesse.

episodes.name: Sokosha
episodes.overview: The Saint corners the trio. Jesse makes a deal with the killer Cowboy. Jesse races to save Tulip and Cassidy.

episodes.name: Pig
episodes.overview: Tulip confronts her near-death experience. Denis asks Cassidy for a favor. Jesse questions the price of saving Cassidy and Tulip.

episodes.name: Holes
episodes.overview: Jesse investigates a fresh clue about God. Tulip makes friends with a new neighbor, and we get a glimpse into Cassidy's past relationship with Denis.

episodes.name: Puzzle Piece
episodes.overview: Jesse gets a much-needed breakthrough on his search for God. Tulip continues to spiral and Cassidy makes a life-altering decision for Denis.

episodes.name: Dirty Little Secret
episodes.overview: Jesse connects with an unlikely source and learns more about God's whereabouts. Tulip can't forgive Jesse when she finds out he's been lying to her.

episodes.name: Backdoors
episodes.overview: The mission begins to alienate Tulip and Cassidy. Tulip receives advice about her relationship with Jesse. Cassidy begins to doubt Denis.

episodes.name: On Your Knees
episodes.overview: Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy hit a bump in the road and decide to leave New Orleans. An old foe resurfaces and causes a change of plans.

episodes.name: The End of the Road
episodes.overview: Jesse questions the path ahead. Tulip uncovers a dangerous secret. Cassidy struggles with a difficult truth.

episodes.name: Angelville
episodes.overview: In an effort to save Tulip, Jesse and Cassidy take her to Jesse's family home, Angelville. Jesse reunites with the people he fears most: his family.

episodes.name: Sonsabitches
episodes.overview: Desperate to escape Angelville and his family, Jesse attempts to forge an unlikely alliance with a familiar adversary.

episodes.name: Gonna Hurt
episodes.overview: While Jesse works to pay back his debt to Gran'ma, Tulip and Cassidy risk their safety as they make their own plans to get out of Angelville.

episodes.name: The Tombs
episodes.overview: As Jesse helps reinvigorate business at Angelville, he tests Tulip and Cassidy's faith in him when Angelville brings out a darker side of him.

episodes.name: The Coffin
episodes.overview: As Cassidy falls in with a group of mysterious strangers in New Orleans, Tulip and Jesse deal with the fallout of a failed escape from Angelville.

episodes.name: Les Enfants du Sang
episodes.overview: Tulip, Jesse, Jody and T.C. hatch an ambitious plan to save both Gran'ma's and Tulip's lives; Cassidy explores a new friendship in New Orleans.

episodes.name: Hilter
episodes.overview: Jesse, Tulip, Gran'ma and Starr form an uneasy partnership to avert the apocalypse; Cassidy learns to love Eccarius, but at a cost.

episodes.name: The Tom/Brady
episodes.overview: Annville, Angelville and the Grail team up to steal souls in New Orleans and Osaka in a last-ditch effort to satisfy Gran'ma and save the world.

episodes.name: Schwanzkopf
episodes.overview: Divided and trapped, Tulip, Jesse and Cassidy battle old friends, new enemies and loved ones to escape certain death - or worse.

episodes.name: The Light Above
episodes.overview: Jesse returns home for what he hopes is the last time but angers Starr and endangers Cassidy in the process; Tulip battles hell and Nazis.

episodes.name: Masada
episodes.overview: Visions of the apocalypse plague Jesse as he and Tulip get ready to strike Masada, where Cassidy is trapped, but Grail and Starr are ready for their assault; Jesse tries to find an unusual rock formation; Tulip attempts to rescue Cassidy.

episodes.name: Last Supper
episodes.overview: Jesse looks for God as the apocalypse looms; Tulip attempts to save Cassidy.

episodes.name: Deviant
episodes.overview: Tulip gets in too deep in Masada; Cassidy reflects on a lost life; the Saint closes in on Jesse.

episodes.name: Search and Rescue
episodes.overview: Tulip forges an unexpected alliance to save Cassidy; Jesse finds himself stranded.

episodes.name: Bleak City
episodes.overview: Tulip reunites with Cassidy and Eugene finds Jesse; the Grail's agenda threatens to unwind.

episodes.name: The Lost Apostle
episodes.overview: Tulip and Cass track Jesse and the Saint of Killers, while Starr searches for the missing messiah.

episodes.name: Messiahs
episodes.overview: Tulip and Cass tear after God; an old friend presents Jesse with an unique opportunity.

episodes.name: Fear of the Lord
episodes.overview: Tulip and Cass struggle to keep Humperdoo hidden from the Grail, while Jesse remains MIA.

episodes.name: Overture
episodes.overview: Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy mount one final assault on Masada as the Apocalypse Revue begins.
